          type="button">
            APPENDIX 1: Extended (Three-Year) Approval Period
        </button>
      </dt>

      <dd class="component-accordion__content component-accordion__content--collapsed"
          aria-labelledby="tab-sectionID-3-5"
          id="panel-sectionID-3-5"
          role="region">

          <div class="component-accordion__content-wrapper">
            <div class="components">

  
    
      

<div class="component  component--is-in-another-component">

  
  <div class="component-text-block">
  
    <div class="component-description">
                    <h2 id="appendix-1-extended-three-year-approval-period" class="__title invisible">APPENDIX 1: Extended (Three-Year) Approval Period</h2>
                    </div>

  
  <p>Effective April 16, 2018 until January 20, 2019, applicable research could be granted an extended or three-year approval period.  The extended approval period was implemented due to the delay of the 2018 Requirements and then stopped when the 2018 Requirements were implemented, including the “no continuing review” provision.  The policy and procedures below were implemented in the April 12, 2018 (Version 3.0) version of the policy.</p>
<ol style="list-style-type: upper-roman">
<li>UIC policy and federal regulations require that IRB-approved research be reviewed at a minimum of once per year (i.e., maximum one year approval period) if the research meets any of the following criteria:
<ol style="list-style-type: upper-alpha">
<li>Federal funding (including no cost extension),</li>
<li>Research is under the oversight of FDA, DoJ, ED, or other agencies that require continuing review at a minimum of once per year,</li>
<li>Greater than minimal risk,</li>
<li>Review by the Convened IRB,</li>
<li>Certificate of Confidentiality has been obtained for the research,</li>
<li>Development Only proposal,</li>
<li>Center or Training grant, or</li>
<li>As per IRB determination.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>As UIC is not obligated to apply the Common Rule to research that is not federally funded, research that does not meet the criteria above may be eligible for an extended approval period of a maximum of three (3) years rather than the one (1) year (or less) period beginning April 16, 2018.
<ol style="list-style-type: upper-alpha">
<li>The IRB determines whether research that currently has a one-year approval may be eligible for the extended approval period at the time of the next Continuing Review.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>Amendments and Prompt Reports must continue to be submitted as applicable in the interim.
<ol style="list-style-type: upper-alpha">
<li>Amendments that change a protocol’s eligibility for the three-year approval period (as stated above) will change the expiration date of the research. For instance, if the amendment adds federal funding to the research then the three-year approval period will be reduced to a one-year approval period.
<ol>
<li>The expiration date will be one year from the date of the approval of the amendment. Approved documents will be stamped with the new approval date or approval period.</li>
<li>Investigators are responsible for ensuring that the most recently approved versions of the documents are being used for recruitment and enrollment purposes.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>Amendments that eliminate the criteria preventing the protocol’s eligibility for the three-year approval period (as stated above) will not increase the approval period (or grant a “no continuing review”) as these determinations can only be determined during the Continuing Review or Initial Review.
<ol>
<li>For instance, an amendment removes federal funding and now could be eligible for a three-year approval as it does not include any of the criteria from above. The amendment would be granted approval without changes to the approval period as an increase in the approval period can only be granted during the Continuing Review.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>



  
</div>

  
</div>

    

</div>
          </div>
      </dd>

    
    </dl>
  </div>

  
</section>

    

</div>

          </article>
        </div>

                                            
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            




   




   
                                 
              
                            
                                 
              

